Certainly! Here's a comforting sentence formatted in LaTeX to console someone who has just failed an exam:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{tcolorbox}
\usepackage{lipsum}

\begin{document}

\begin{center}
\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=blue!5!white, colframe=blue!75!black, width=0.75\textwidth, boxrule=0.5mm, sharp corners]
    \centering
    \textit{\textbf{\large{Remember, failure is not the opposite of success, it is part of success. Keep your head up, and keep moving forward.}}}
\end{tcolorbox}
\end{center}

\end{document}
```

This code uses the `tcolorbox` package to create a visually appealing box with a comforting message in the center of the document. The message is italicized and bolded to stand out, and the box is styled with a light blue background and a darker blue border.
